# A7-Loops-and-Numbers

Create a program that will ask the user to enter a positive number and counts. The program will
end the loop once the user enters a non-positive value and then display the sum of the numbers. (use
do-while statement).

package com.BasicJavaprograms;
import java.util.*;
public class positiveNumberandCounts {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		
		try (Scanner Scan = new Scanner (System.in)) {
			System.out.println("Enter number 1: 45");
			System.out.println("Enter number 2: 23");
			System.out.println("Enter number 3: 76");
			System.out.println("Enter number 4: 80");
			System.out.println("Enter number 5: 10");
			System.out.println("Enter number 6: 0");
			double m = Scan.nextDouble();
		}
		int i = 637;
		
		do {
			 System.out.println(i);
			 i++;
		}
		 while (i>=6);
		
		System.out.println("You enter 5 numbers");{
